headline: PayPal, Duolingo, Meta: Trending Tickers
summary: PayPal (PYPL) is in focus after the company announced plans to enable crypto payments for over 100 digital currencies, allowing merchants to accept options like bitcoin (BTC-USD) and ethereum (ETH-USD). Duolingo (DUOL) stock is under pressure following a price target cut by Citizens JMP Securities, citing slowing user engagement since April. Meta's (META) price target was raised to $800 by Guggenheim, citing investor confidence in the company's artificial intelligence (AI) strategy. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination here.
